# Format: <pattern> <owner>
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ============================================================================
# GLOBAL DEFAULT OWNER
# ============================================================================
# Primary fallback owner for any path (solo founder until team ≥3 engineers):
* @jay13jay

# ============================================================================
# GOVERNANCE & SECURITY (Always requires founder approval)
# ============================================================================
# ADRs and architecture decisions:
docs/decisions/ @jay13jay

# Security policies and sensitive configs:
SECURITY.md @jay13jay
.github/workflows/ @jay13jay
.github/CODEOWNERS @jay13jay

# ============================================================================
# AREA-SPECIFIC OWNERSHIP (Activate when scaling to teams)
# ============================================================================
# When creating @org/backend team, uncomment:
# /api/ @org/backend
# /services/ @org/backend
# /migrations/ @org/backend
# /database/ @org/backend

# When creating @org/frontend team, uncomment:
# /ui/ @org/frontend
# /web/ @org/frontend
# /components/ @org/frontend
# /client/ @org/frontend

# When creating @org/platform team, uncomment:
# /infra/ @org/platform @jay13jay
# /terraform/ @org/platform @jay13jay
# /k8s/ @org/platform @jay13jay
# /.github/ @org/platform @jay13jay
# /deployments/ @org/platform @jay13jay

# ============================================================================
# MIGRATION PATH
# ============================================================================
# Solo (now): All ownership via @jay13jay catch-all above
# First hire (3-6mo): Keep individual assignments, no teams yet
# 3+ engineers: Create teams, uncomment relevant sections above
# 5+ engineers: Replace catch-all with: * @org/engineering
